<TITLE> 117 made OSDs, House told </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 29 (bdnews24.com)Some 117 civil servants from secretary to deputy secretary level have been made OSDs under the new government, the establishment minister told parliament on Sunday. Syed Ashraful Islam said none secretary, 31additional secretary, 43 joint secretary, and 34 deputy secretary-level officials have been made OSDs, in reply to a question from Mohammad Fazlul Azim MP. Meanwhile, the law minister told parliament that a total of 452 persons accused of corruption received clemency from the Truth Commission in exchange for fines during the immediate past care-taker government. Shafiq Ahmed also apprised the House that the government has taken initiates to lessen case jam, including creation of posts for judges and filling vacant posts. In reply to a query from Mujibur Rahman Fakir MP, the law minister also said steps were underway to finally execute the Bangabandhu murder case verdict with the recent appointment of two new judges to the Appellate Division. The appeal hearing will resume soon, he said. Shahfiq also said the government is moving to establish a permanent office for the Human Rights Commission and the HRC bill has been raised in the House to this effect. bdnew
